value.0: The following list of commands that can be used by the Dungeon Master. To use each command simply hit the <StartCheck>~ key</Start>, and type in the command. You will notice that hitting the ~ key only brings up a cursor in the upper left-hand corner of your screen to continue typing.

These functions will activate action target mode. The target you click will have its stat/save set to N.

dm_setCHA N
dm_setCON N
dm_setDEX N
dm_setINT N
dm_setSTR N
dm_setWIS N

dm_setCR N
dm_setattackbase N
dm_setspellresistance N

These functions will activate action target mode. The target you click will have the stat/save adjusted by N. Positive values will cause an increase, while negative values will cause a decrease.

dm_modifyCHA N 
dm_modifyCON N
dm_modifyDEX N
dm_modifyINT N
dm_modifySTR N
dm_modifyWIS N

dm_modifyattackbase N
dm_modifysavefortitude N
dm_modifysavereflex N
dm_modifysavewill N
dm_modifyspellresistance N
Which tool do you want to check?
Adjusts a player's reputation with Forrstakrr NPCs. Simple enough

to rule them all... Or not. This item is actually used to change area settings such as fog, fog colour, area lighting, etcetera. A neat little tool! Make sure you reload the area to check after you're done, as sometimes it -does- bug and give you the wrong settings. Especially true for fog density.
If people are loitering in the entry, use this. it forces them to go in game.
Simple enough. Use it on a placable/NPC/item and it will be destroyed. Some items have an awesome destroy image, by the way.

This tool has some of the abilities of the DM Info Tool, and a few other abilities. Any confirmed Amia Module Tester is to be granted one of these on request. They allow an array of statistics and information to be presented as may be required of a tester.
Same as the Skin Changer, except it's a skin/portrait changer for summons that activates automatically. Instructions are on the item!

This is, as you can see, an unset skin changer widget. The instructions are on the item. If a player requests a custom-skin and gets it approved by the DM Team, this tool is used to create the widget for it. Instructions are on the item's description!

A Portal Rod with unlimited uses. Simple as that. While in the DM Client, this tool can be used to force-port someone by using it directly on them too. Fun for plots, especially the 'random location' one!

A simple little tool which is good if you want temporary visual effects. It can create coloured shafts of light, magical sparks, flames, etcetera which remain for a duration of either 1, 3, 5, or 10 minutes.

A workaround to the known problem of player-list bugging, the Jump DM To Player tool will give you a list of all online players, first categorized in ABC order. Click their name, and boom you're there. 
Jump Player to DM works the same way, except it ports them to you instead of the other way around.

The DM tool: Our standard means of handing out dream coins. Quite simple and to the point. Use it on someone, it'll give you a convo with various options on granting/removing Dcs. Use it on yourself to get a list of people who have been recommended for good RP. 

The PC tool: Using it on yourself will give you DC-Burning options. Using it on someone else will recommend them for Dream Coins.
Simple little doo-dad. Use it on someone, then click on a location. That player will fly there. Simple as that.

This tool, when used, will pause an area for a moderate duration. All creatures become force-paralyzed, unable to do anything (even if they have freedom or immunities). PCs glow Blue, hostile creatures glow red, and allied creatures glow green. This is an alternative measure to the standard DM Client Pause which affects the entire server.
